10 月终止</a>后<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/jay-z-is-last-rapper-on-forbes-billionaire-list-after-kanye-falls-off-3427600">，Jay-Z 成为唯一一位出现在<em>福布斯</em>亿万富翁排行榜上的说唱歌手</a>。</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/jay-z-is-reportedly-interested-in-buying-tottenham-hotspur-fc-3475657">据报道，Jay-Z 有兴趣收购托特纳姆热刺队的帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
波斯特·马龙讲述了迷幻蘑菇的使用如何影响他的记忆https://www.nme.com/news/music/post-malone-on-how-magic-mushroom-use-has-affected-memory-3475815?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=post-malone-on-how-使用魔法蘑菇影响记忆Liberty DunworthMon, 31 Jul 2023 16:41:31 +0000 Music NewsNewsRap https://www.nme.com/?p=3475815 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Post-Malone-rapper-2000-x-1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="波斯特·马龙现场表演" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Post-Malone-rapper-2000-x-1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Post-Malone-rapper-2000-x-1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Post-Malone-rapper-2000-x-1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Post-Malone-rapper-2000-x-1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Post-Malone-rapper-2000-x-1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Post-Malone-rapper-2000-x-1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>他还解释了父亲身份如何帮助他缓和摇滚明星的生活方式</p><p>波斯特<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/post-malone-on-how-magic-mushroom-use-has-affected-memory-3475815">·马龙（Post Malone）关于使用迷幻蘑菇如何影响他的记忆力的帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">《NME》</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Post-Malone-rapper-2000-x-1270.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="波斯特·马龙现场表演" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Post-Malone-rapper-2000-x-1270.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Post-Malone-rapper-2000-x-1270-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Post-Malone-rapper-2000-x-1270-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Post-Malone-rapper-2000-x-1270-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Post-Malone-rapper-2000-x-1270-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/02/Post-Malone-rapper-2000-x-1270-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/post-malone">波斯特·马龙</a>揭示了使用迷幻蘑菇如何影响他的短期记忆。</p><ul><li><strong>阅读更多：<a href="https://www.nme.com/features/music-features/post-malone-best-songs-3473559">波斯特·马龙：10 首歌中的纹身游吟诗人的故事</a></strong></li></ul><p>这位说唱歌手周三（7 月 26 日）在接受 Apple Music 的 Zane Lowe 的新采访时透露，他患有迷幻蘑菇的长期副作用。</p><p> “是的，我拿蘑菇，”他告诉洛。 “我喜欢蘑菇……[但]不像以前那么喜欢了。 It&#39;s really affected my short-term memory. Maybe it was just a stint of habitual overuse. Daily. But now I take a little bar of chocolate with my buddies, a little square chocolate and just laugh and laugh and laugh.”</p><p> He continued, explaining how he has seen the drug used to treat people suffering from PTSD, and how he believes it can often lead to a more &#39;positive&#39; response than pharmaceuticals.</p><p> “I was talking to a ranger buddy of mine. He was a ranger and he was saying they&#39;re giving it to guys for PTSD and stuff. And I was like, oh that&#39;s cool because a lot of the times, a lot of pharmaceuticals, they have negative reactions often,” he explained. “It&#39;s cool to see that they&#39;re giving them this medicine and it&#39;s actually working.</p><p> “He was saying his buddy was going through it and it really helped him a lot. I don&#39;t know. It&#39;s interesting because it&#39;s improved. It has improved my view on things.” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="波斯特·马龙：《奥斯汀》、《外星人与父亲》|苹果音乐" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/0RkLROuLtxs?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> Elsewhere in the discussion, Malone also reflected on how his outlook has become more optimistic in his latest album <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/post-malone-austin-review-3474831">&#39;Austin&#39;</a> , and explored the ways in which having a child has pushed him to tone down his reckless lifestyle.</p><p> “Making the last record – well, writing it – I was so, so sad. But now I&#39;m so happy and it&#39;s definitely improved my viewpoint on life,” he admitted. “Having a baby really put a lot into perspective, and it&#39;s really slowed me down a lot, party-wise, going out and being crazy.</p><p> “I just want to take some time now,” he continued. “And actually you mentioned all the accoutrements of success and everything that comes with that. Now I just want to take a second and enjoy it.”</p><p> The comments regarding his stance on drugs come following various concerns from fans in recent years. He previously admitted to struggling with alcoholism and, <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/post-malone-addresses-fans-recent-concern-over-his-health-2621886">back in 2020, fans took to social media to show their worry for the musician after he was seen stumbling, slurring his words and rolling his eyes back</a> whilst performing in Memphis.</p><p> The rapper later took to the stage and addressed the comments – denying ever being on drugs and saying he felt “the best I&#39;ve ever fucking felt in my life”.</p><p> Concerns arose again in April of this year when he was <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/post-malone-says-he-isnt-on-drugs-dad-life-kicked-in-3436886">speculated to be on drugs after losing a significant amount of weight</a> . </p><blockquote class="instagram-media" data-instgrm-captioned data-instgrm-permalink="https://www.instagram.com/p/CrkBEkqq4nk/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading" data-instgrm-version="14" style=" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:658px; min-width:326px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 